	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=88312><span id=Scholar>Slaton</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>30 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>To further clarify my previous statements, there is a reason I am in the back with the casters, The casters or the Cleric WILL agro something eventualy, from Chain nukeing, or Chain healing, or something.&nbsp;&nbsp;I  am back out of the fight to serve as an 'overwatch' to protect the casters.   Then your job is to intercept it.  Many fights with 2 or 3 mobs no one knows the cleric/wiz is getting hit because everyone is concentrating on the mobs infront and no one sees the one that breaks off.  And no one hears the caster yell till he is 1/2 dead, then it's a frantic rush to get to the wizard and help.  (ever see a Sabertooth hit a wizard... not pretty)<br><br>Reason number 2 that you are back there, to watch for, and intercept adds. This is mainly in outdoor zones (LOIO or OT are excellent examples).  When an add is going to agro on the group, you drop an arrow on it, take your sowed butt half way across the zone, snare it, then track your way back to your group at SOW speed.  thus nutralising the add for atleast a little while, or an alternative (if the group is ok with out you) is to just bowkite it or fear kite (if you are luck enough to have an animal comming on you) for awhile until your group is done with the one it's on.<br><br>Continualy checking track is vary distracting in combat, looking for named/rare spawns to pull to the group, We all do this right?<br><br>Those are the reasons you are back there, not to pound on the primary target, but to handle the 2nd, 3rd or (on realy bad days) 4th MOB that happens to come along.  Also since we are invarably pullers, it means you can eaisly bugger out to continue the chain pulling when the mob is getting worn down.<br><br>As for a lack of damage with bows, well perhaps your dex is not high enough?  It seems to effect damage much the same way that str effects melie damage.    Mine is (aprox) 175 with all my gear on and at 30th level, with bow skill maxed i hit for 45 to 50 with cheap arrows (2 dmg), throw on good arrows (for whenyou need a little more kick, 5 or 6 damage, but pricy to make) and i hit in the low 50s consistently.  Add the uped number of crits (funny how many dex/agi items there are huh?) and about 1 shot out of 4 is for over 100 damage.<br><br>As far as the 'not doing the most damage' is concerned, well perhaps you are correct, perhaps I could do more damage up front, stacked with str items and slashing away in the gore and guts of some sarnak or giant, but I have no problem finding groups, esp after i have been in zone for a day or two and saved a few casters butts, and pulled a few named from half way across the zone, funny how much ppl like you when you pull targets that have good drops huh?<br><br>But that's just me, play your ranger as you like to, i mean this is a Role playing game, don't play a ranger how i do if you do not want to.<br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Slaton--Pallidan 52nd Rank--<br>Corton-- Ranger 34th<br> Season--<br></td></td></tr>
