	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>161 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.14]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Sure you can cast while meleeing.&nbsp;&nbsp;You cast inbetween swings.  With a pair of moderately fast 1h'ers, you will delay your swings a little, but not horribly.  And since the weapon delay and casting was untied (weapon delay is independent of casting spells), you do not have to wait a full delay cycle to swing again.  For example, if you wield a pair of Yaks (8/24) and cast Careless lightning (2.7 cast) you add 99 dmg if it is not partially or fully resisted while "losing" .3 delay worth of weapon attacks.  Not bad if you ask me.  <br><br>This is especially good with a 2h slash weapon that has a delay of around 40.  You will never even notice you are casting as it pertains to your weapon swinging.  Swing, start 40 delay count.  Start casting 10 delay into it.  Spell goes off at 37 delay.  You swing at 40.  And you never missed a beat =)<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Davall<br>42 Ranger BB</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
