	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>161 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.14]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I can say with 100% certainty that the weapon delay and spells for HYBRIDS are untied.&nbsp;&nbsp;As soon as your spell goes off, if enough time has passed for your weapon delay to have been met, you will swing immediately.  Try it out.  Swing and immediately cast a long cast time spell (a buff works great for this).  When the spell goes off, you will swing right after.  They realized Hybrids were losing a lot of damage because the weapon would start the delay countdown after the spell was finished.  For example, carelss lightning taking 2.7 seconds to cast and having a yak (2.4 seconds) would cost you a total of 5.1 seconds, UNDER THE OLD SYSTEM.  That is a lot of damage missed to cast a spell and it hurt.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Davall<br>42 Ranger BB</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
